com.fasterxml.cachemate
Interface CacheEntry<K,V>

All Known Subinterfaces:
TwoKeyCacheEntry<K1,K2,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
POJOCacheEntry, TwoKeyPOJOCacheEntry
public interface CacheEntry<K,V>

Entry for cache; contains both _key and value, to reduce number of object instances needed. Also provides metadata useful for caller.ache

getExpirationInMilliSeconds

long getExpirationInMilliSeconds(long currentTime)
Accessor for getting an estimate of how long this entry may still be retained (and accessible) by the cache element. Can be used for things like refreshers that try to re-load new value before expiration. Note that some backends may not be able to provide accurate estimate; possibly not even any. If so, any value between initial TTL and 0L is acceptable return value

Parameters:
currentTime - Current time as reported by {link System.currentTimeMillis() (or provided as part of testing, simulation)
Returns:
Approximate time until entry expires, in milliseconds.
Since:
0.5.0
